depthLimitedSearch

private Result depthLimitedSearch(java.lang.String word,
                                  java.lang.String goal,
                                  int currentDepth,
                                  int maxDepth)
Implementation of depth-limited search algorithm. Used by both generation and discovery methods to generate paths. If a target node is not specified, the search will continue until it reaches the maximum depth, then quits.

Parameters:
word - The current node being looked at
goal - The target node
currentDepth - The current depth in the graph
maxDepth - The maximum depth to descend before quitting the search
Returns:
